Talisman Lionel Messi has returned to the training of Barcelona for the first time since the transfer row, which ended last Friday. Messi had informed the club he wanted to leave, claiming he was a free agent but the Catalan giants insisted his $700 million release clause must be paid for him to leave. He made a U-turn on Friday, insisting he wanted a move but won’t force a divorce with the club of his life. On Monday, he was back at the training camp of the club. To show his commitment to the club, he was the first to arrive the training pitch more than one hour before others. Lionel MessiThe Nation Barcelona - Lionel Messi was back training on Saturday, although he did not join the session with his Barcelona team-mates. Messi had missed the Friday session at the club’s Joan Gamper Football City and Barcelona said “the captain has a small muscle contraction in the quadriceps of his right leg`’’.… June 6, 2020 In "Sports" Barcelona - Lionel Messi’s father and agent met Barcelona Club President Josep Maria Bartomeu on Wednesday to discuss the player’s wish to leave the club but the talks ended in stalemate, Spanish media reported. Earlier, Jorge Messi said it would be “difficult” for his son to remain with Barcelona, the… September 3, 2020 In "Sports" Barcelona - Jorge Messi, Lionel`s father and agent says it will be difficult for his son to remain at FC Barcelona after he made public his desire to leave the Spanish club. He said this as he arrived in the city to negotiate his son’s future on Wednesday. After flying… September 2, 2020 In "Sports"